                  <h1>
                    Frequently Asked Questions
                  </h1>
                  
                  <h4>What are my rights over content I post to Piazza?</h4>
                  <p>You retain complete control over your content. Furthermore, if instructors request that their courses be completely deleted, we do not retain any information, including posts, from them.</p>

                  <h4>Is my class discussion accessible via a search engine?</h4>
                  <p>No, your class discussion is not available or accessible via search engines.</p>


                  <h4>Can I use Piazza for [non-academic, non-university, etc.] purposes?</h4>
                  <p>Absolutely, the Piazza Q&amp;A forum has been successfully used by high schools, companies, faculty for departmental discussions, after-school programs, teams, etc. The “instructors” can name the courses whatever they like, and choose any course number they find appropriate. It is not restricted to university/academic purposes.</p>

